<TITLE> Poet Askar Ibn Sheikh dies </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 18 (bdnews24.com)Poet Askar Ibn Sheikh died on Monday at a hospital in the city from old-age complications at 86, his wife told bdnews24.com. He was laid to rest at the graveyard of Dhaka City Corporation at Mohammadpur following Namaz-e-Janaza after Zohr prayers. He won many prizes, including Bangla Academy Prize, Ekushey Padak, and Islamic Foundation Award. He served as a teacher of Department of Statistics at the University of Dhaka and University of Jahangirnagar. Sheikh, according to Bangla Academy Dictionary of Writers, has around 38 books on society, history, lyrics, poetry and teleplay
